{"add":{"doc":{"id":"f44d0b845ae548e305330895283a90313e15b6e8ff18600fd209524c4e9d2a57","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0a/Hollywood_Sign_PB050006.jpg/220px-Hollywood_Sign_PB050006.jpg","previous":[],"after":["Hollywood, a northern district of Los Angeles, California, is one of the leaders in motion picture production.[471] The world's first commercial motion picture exhibition was given in New York City in 1894, using Thomas Edison's Kinetoscope.[472] The next year saw the first commercial screening of a projected film, also in New York, and the United States was in the forefront of sound film's development in the following decades. Since the early 20th century, the U.S. film industry has largely been based in and around Hollywood, although in the 21st century an increasing number of films are not made there, and film companies have been subject to the forces of globalization.[473]"]}}}